data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ggb1665702752849.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ggb1665702752849.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ggb1665702752849.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ggb1665702752849\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Configuring the SOAP Connector\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When call-in out to SOAP-based web services, you need to choose a Uniface SOAP connector and configure it.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__context_w6037ab1b5b1_w6038ab1b5_w6039ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__topic_d37241e1_d37242e1_d37243e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__p_d37244e1_d37245e1_d37246e1\">The Uniface SOAP U2.0 connector supports different\n               binding styles. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ukw1665702547648.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ukw1665702547648.html\" title=\"The Web Services Description Language (WSDL) is an XML-based language for describing Web services and how to access them.\">WSDL</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__li_d18977e1_d18978e1_d18979e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To use SOAP connector U2.0, ensure that the following setting is present in the client assignment file:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nSOP U2.0</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__li_d18989e1_d18990e1_d18991e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, specify connector options and call-out component parameters:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__li_d18992e1_d18993e1_d18994e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section, specify connector-wide options for the SOAP\n                     connector using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$SOP_PARAMS</span> setting. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kxm1665702543272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kxm1665702543272.html\" title=\"You can set the default SOAP connector options using the USYS$SOP_PARAMS setting in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file. They can be overridden for specific components in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section and they can be set dynamically using the $signatureproperties ProcScript function.\">SOAP Connector Options</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__li_d18995e1_d18996e1_d18997e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__p_d37247e1_d37248e1_d37249e1\">In the [SERVICES_EXEC] section, specify\n                     parameters for specific components that will be executing call-out to Web\n                     services. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Settings in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section override the corresponding connector\n                        options specified in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section. The connector options in\n                           <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$SOP_PARAMS</span> cannot be nullified; they can only be\n                        overridden with another value.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__note_w6040ab1b5b3b5b3b3b3b3_w6041ab1b5b3b5b3b3b3_w6042ab1b5b3b5b3b3_w6043ab1b5b3b5b3_w6044ab1b5b3b5_w6045ab1b5b3_w6046ab1b5_w6047ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If your SOAP service uses entity or occurrence parameters, it is\n                        not possible to reassign it to another application in the [SERVICES_EXEC]\n                        section. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujx1665702543107.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujx1665702543107.html\" title=\"Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components.\">[SERVICES_EXEC]</a>.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__li_d18998e1_d18999e1_d19000e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ggb1665702752849__p_d37250e1_d37251e1_d37252e1\">To call out to web services from a Uniface\n               Server, add the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/su</span> switch in the Uniface Server's UST in the\n               Uniface Router's assignment file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">This prevents problems with permissions. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/su</span> switch causes\n                  the Uniface Server to start in the environment of the user rather than in the\n                  environment of the Uniface Router.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kxm1665702543272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SOAP Connector Options</a><p>You can set the default SOAP connector options using the USYS$SOP_PARAMS setting in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file. They can be overridden for specific components in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section and they can be set dynamically using the $signatureproperties ProcScript function.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tha1665702897542.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-Out from Uniface to a Web Service</a><p>A Uniface application can call a Web service via the Uniface SOAP connector.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/msq1665702542189.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[DRIVER_SETTINGS]</a><p>Use the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file to specify the database and component engine connectors used, and their parameter options. The options available depend on the connector in use.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujx1665702543107.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[SERVICES_EXEC]</a><p>Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/idu1665702544495.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/su</a><p>Direct the Uniface Router to start the Uniface Server in the environment of the user.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527838\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527838\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the SOAP Connector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring the SOAP Connector When call-in out to SOAP-based web services, you need to choose a Uniface SOAP connector and configure it. The Uniface SOAP U2.0 connector supports different binding styles. For more information, see WSDL . To use SOAP connector U2.0, ensure that the following setting is present in the client assignment file: [DRIVER_SETTINGS] SOP U2.0 Copy Optionally, specify connector options and call-out component parameters: In the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section, specify connector-wide options for the SOAP connector using the USYS$SOP_PARAMS setting. For more information, see SOAP Connector Options . In the [SERVICES_EXEC] section, specify parameters for specific components that will be executing call-out to Web services. Settings in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section override the corresponding connector options specified in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section. The connector options in USYS$SOP_PARAMS cannot be nullified; they can only be overridden with another value. Note: If your SOAP service uses entity or occurrence parameters, it is not possible to reassign it to another application in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section. For more information, see [SERVICES_EXEC] . To call out to web services from a Uniface Server, add the /su switch in the Uniface Server's UST in the Uniface Router's assignment file. This prevents problems with permissions. The /su switch causes the Uniface Server to start in the environment of the user rather than in the environment of the Uniface Router. Related Links SOAP Connector Options You can set the default SOAP connector options using the USYS$SOP_PARAMS setting in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file. They can be overridden for specific components in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section and they can be set dynamically using the $signatureproperties ProcScript function. Call-Out from Uniface to a Web Service A Uniface application can call a Web service via the Uniface SOAP connector. [DRIVER_SETTINGS] Use the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file to specify the database and component engine connectors used, and their parameter options. The options available depend on the connector in use. [SERVICES_EXEC] Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components. /su Direct the Uniface Router to start the Uniface Server in the environment of the user. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}